# ToolAdvisor Automation Context\
\
## Purpose\
\
This project is not only about improving ToolAdvisor manually.\
\
The goal is to build a controlled agent-based workflow where Murat acts as the product owner and decision maker, while Claude Code and Codex execute research, planning, implementation, QA and reporting tasks through a structured automation flow.\
\
Murat should not manually track every file, every decision, every GitHub result or every task.  \
The system must make this operationally visible and controlled.\
\
## Core Objective\
\
ToolAdvisor must become a professional cutting-tools decision platform.\
\
It is not a generic catalogue, not a webshop, and not a blog.\
\
The product direction is:\
\
- brand-neutral cutting tool selection\
- product comparison\
- cross-reference logic\
- product detail intelligence\
- data confidence layer\
- trusted recommendation reasoning\
- controlled product data growth\
- no blind scraping\
- no uncontrolled PRODUCT_DB changes\
\
## Working Model\
\
The intended workflow is:\
\
1. Murat gives an idea, direction or decision in natural language.\
2. The agent system converts that input into a structured task.\
3. The correct agent type is selected:\
   - Claude Code for planning, architecture, research, review, documentation and reasoning-heavy work.\
   - Codex for implementation, code changes, tests and controlled file edits.\
4. The agent reads the required control files.\
5. The agent executes only the approved task.\
6. The agent updates the worklog.\
7. GitHub Actions checks the result.\
8. Murat reviews the outcome and decides:\
   - approve\
   - reject\
   - revise\
   - continue\
\
Murat should mainly decide direction, priority and approval.  \
Agents should handle execution and reporting.\
\
## Current Control Files\
\
These files define the operating rules:\
\
- `CLOUDFLARE_MIGRATION.md`\
- `TOOLADVISOR_WORKLOG.md`\
- `AGENT_PROTOCOL.md`\
\
Before doing anything, every agent must read:\
\
- `CLOUDFLARE_MIGRATION.md`\
- `TOOLADVISOR_WORKLOG.md`\
- `AGENT_PROTOCOL.md`\
\
If a decision is unclear or not covered, the agent must stop and ask.\
