## Immediate Next Direction\
\
The next major step is not random UI work.\
\
The next strategic step is to build the Agent Dispatcher layer.\
\
## Agent Dispatcher Goal\
\
Create a system/process where Murat\'92s natural language request can be converted into a structured task file.\
\
The dispatcher must decide:\
\
- is this a research task?\
- is this a planning task?\
- is this an implementation task?\
- is this a QA task?\
- should Claude Code handle it?\
- should Codex handle it?\
- should it stop and ask?\
- what files are allowed?\
- what files are forbidden?\
- what output is expected?\
- should GitHub Actions be checked?\
- should worklog be updated?\
\
## Required Next Files\
\
Create or refine:\
\
- `AGENT_DISPATCHER.md`\
- `tasks/template.md`\
- `research/004-agent-dispatcher-plan.md`\
\
Do not modify production files for this step.\
\
## Task Flow\
\
Each task should follow this flow:\
\
1. `tasks/todo/`\
2. `tasks/in-progress/`\
3. execution\
4. QA / postflight\
5. worklog update\
6. `tasks/done/` or `tasks/blocked/`\
7. GitHub Actions result\
8. Murat decision\
\
## Task Types\
\
### Research Task\
\
Used for market research, schema review, feature investigation, product strategy.\
\
Usually handled by Claude Code.\
\
No production changes.\
\
### Planning Task\
\
Used for implementation plans, migration strategy, risk analysis, architecture.\
\
Usually handled by Claude Code.\
\
No production changes unless explicitly approved.\
\
### Implementation Task\
\
Used for actual code or data structure changes.\
\
Usually handled by Codex.\
\
Must define allowed files and forbidden files.\
\
### QA Task\
\
Used for browser testing, console checks, regression checks, GitHub Actions interpretation.\
\
Can be handled by Claude Code or Codex.\
\
No production changes unless explicitly approved.\
\
## Stop Conditions\
\
Agent must stop if:\
\
- active root is unclear\
- requested change touches `PRODUCT_DB`\
- task requires deploy\
- task requires Netlify\
- production file changes are not explicitly allowed\
- multiple conflicting source files exist\
- GitHub Actions fails and reason is unclear\
- task conflicts with `CLOUDFLARE_MIGRATION.md`\
- task conflicts with `AGENT_PROTOCOL.md`\
\
## GitHub Role\
\
GitHub is the control and visibility layer.\
\
It should show:\
\
- what changed\
- whether guard passed\
- whether forbidden files changed\
- whether `PRODUCT_DB` was touched\
- whether Netlify files appeared\
- whether worklog was updated\
\
Murat should be able to look at GitHub and decide approve/reject/revise.\
\
## Owner Role\
\
Murat\'92s role:\
\
- set product direction\
- decide priority\
- approve/reject/revise results\
- decide when deploy is allowed\
- decide when PRODUCT_DB may be changed\
- decide when a feature is accepted\
\
Murat should not manually inspect every small technical detail unless flagged.\
\
